@node "INTRO" "iNTRODUCTiON"

                                  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 dCN!MsgScan is a Masterpiece of tool/door for the use with a FAME BBS!
 Granted, the Demo-version, isn't that much great, but when you have
 the registered one, you will be ..... have no words for....

 With this tool, you can search for a specific string in the messagebase
 or in the message-text's. You can choose the direction to search (Forward
 or Backward), you can even choose, if you want to search case sensitive or
 case insensitive, what at last is a matter of speed performance of this Tool.

 When scanning through the mails, you can delete the mails, or devert the
 mail to a new receiver (as example to you're self, to save old mails).

 It's fucking fast, and doesn't eat to much memory.
 So install it, and enjoy it... 
                               signed, Derrow (dCN-/F·dEZiGN)!

 See @{"iNSTALLATION" link "INSTALL" 0} for more information.

@endnode

@node "REQUIRE" "rEQUIREMENTS"

                     @{b}@{u}Requirements for dCN!MsgScan v1.0 usage@{ub}@{uu}

 - An Amiga with operating system V2.04+

 - FAME Mailbox Mainpart v1.9+ 
   FAME Mailbox System Editor v1.2+ 
   FAME Mailbox Server v1.4+

   That's all!

@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "iNSTALLATION"

                                  @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}


 To install this fine piece of work, do the following:

 Use the installer supported within this archive, or copy manual the 
 @{"Contents" link "CONTENTS" 0} of this archive to the following directory's:

 Just copy all files from FAME:
                               ...to your "FAME:" assignment.


 If you have a 68020 or higher processor in your fine Amiga,
 use the ".020+" version instead!.
@endnode

